    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen `cursorline` is set to true, scrolling past function implementations breaks their highlighting. See images\n\nCursor on the bottom, broken\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e389465f-257e-47a1-b251-7d372a695000)\n\nCursor at the top, works\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7d4edae7-e57b-409e-a28d-43eb531f405c)\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/aba0b8d8-1713-4d2e-956c-ce7d96664f48\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nCreate a haskell file (.hs) with the contents\n```haskell\ndata Foobar = Foobar {one :: String, two :: String}\n\nfoo :: Int\nfoo = 7 -- Turns white when scrolled past\n\nfoofoo :: Int\nfoofoo = 0 -- Turns white when scrolled past\n\nbar :: String\nbar = \"foo\"\n```\nOpen it using this config\n```lua\n-- Run this file as `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n  'https://github.com/ellisonleao/gruvbox.nvim',\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\nvim.opt.cursorline = true\n\nrequire(\"gruvbox\").setup({})\n\nvim.cmd([[colorscheme gruvbox]])\n\nrequire(\"nvim-treesitter.configs\").setup({\n    highlight = { enable = true },\n})\n```\nScroll past the function implementations, putting the cursor either at the top or bottom.\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe functions shouldn't change in color, it should only highlight the current line\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1741730670 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, treesitter is needed\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixos 25.11.20250621.4206c4c\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.15.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nInstalled via the nixvim nixos module",
